PRIVACY POLICY

GENERAL PROVISIONS

Your privacy is important to us. This privacy statement explains what information we may collect from you and how we use it, whom we share it with, and the controls we give you to access, update, and delete your information. In other words, this Policy describes policy of in relation to the personal data processing and security of Global Foginfo Technology CO Limited, Suite 603, 6/F Laws Comm Plaza 788 Cheung Sha Wan RD KLN, Hong Kong CHINA (hereinafter “Foginfo”, “We”, “Us”) in respect of the data collected and processed within Oh My Vap applications and Oh My Vap websites (hereinafter – “Oh My Vap”, “Oh My Vap Services”, “Services”).
The Policy defines general principles and the order of personal data processing within Oh My Vap as well as security measures performed by Foginfo.
The aim of the Policy is to ensure the protection of rights and liberties of human and citizens with regard to his/her personal data processing, including privacy protection of right to a private life, personal and family confidentiality.
The Policy is applicable to the Oh My Vap users in those cases where the relations with them are governed by the legislation of the Russian Federation. The Policy is prepared in accordance with the Federal Law of the Russian Federation dated of July 27, 2006 No. 152-FZ “On personal data”(the “Personal Data Law”) as well as other legal acts of the Russian Federation which establish requirements to personal data processing.
Foginfo has the right to amend the Policy. The date of the last amendment shall be indicated in the item “Policy Version” with specification of the date of the amendment. This date means the effective date of the new version of the Policy. We will notify you about the amendment of the Policy. If you continue to use Oh My Vap Services, this means that you agree with the amended version of the Policy.
