Sensitive Personal Information
Certain information, such as information about your race or ethnic origin, religious or philosophical views or personal health, is characterized as “sensitive” and is subject to stricter regulation than other personal information. Please note that consent and information that you input to our Services, such as photographs or information about your school or social activities, may reveal your sensitive personal information to others.

We urge you to consider whether it is appropriate to communicate personal information of a sensitive nature in the manner you are proposing to communicate it using our Services.

You consent to all processing of sensitive personal information for the purposes and in the manner described in this Privacy Policy once you share it and make it publicly available within the Services.

Please note that we do not specifically collect process or use your sensitive personal information and discourage you from sharing it.
Third-Party Services on Our Services
Our Services may link you to other social media or other services provided by third party, for example: you may be able to share content on, or log in, our Services using services provided by third parties. The third parties who provide such services may be able to collect your information and personal information (including your log data), and may set cookies on your computer to enable such feature to function properly; and we may (whether in advertisements or otherwise within our Services) provide you with links that allow you to access third party services or websites.

ABOUT COOKIES & SIMILAR TECHNOLOGIES
Our Services may use cookies and other technologies, such as web beacons, web storage, and unique advertising identifiers, to collect information about your activity, browser, and device. We may also use these technologies to collect information when you interact with Services we offer through one of our partners. Most of the web browsers are set to accept cookies by default. Should you prefer, you usually should be able to remove or reject browser cookies through the settings on your browser or device. Please keep in mind, that removing or rejecting cookies could affect the availability and functionality of our Services. Oh My Vap SERVICES’ COOKIES DO NOT AND CANNOT INFILTRATE A USER'S HARD DRIVE TO GATHER A USER'S CONFIDENTIAL INFORMATION. OUR COOKIES ARE NOT "SPYWARE."

MINORS UNDER 18
We love young people. HOWEVER, minors under the age of 18 shall NOT use our Services. Again, our Services are not intended for, and we don’t direct them to anyone under 18. We do NOT knowingly collect personal information from any minors under the age of 18. Please contract our privacy officer at  service@Oh My Vap.com if you believe we have any personal information from any children under the age of 18 and we will promptly investigate (and remove) such personal information.

TRANSFER, STORAGE AND SECURITY OF YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION

We operate and may continue to operate Oh My Vap Services in a number of jurisdictions around the world, so the server on which your purposes described in this Privacy Policy.

We use a variety of security technologies and procedures for purpose of preventing loss, misuse, unauthorized access or disclosure of information.

In our Services, we will use encryption technology (such as ssl) to protect certain sensitive information (such as location data) provided by you to us. Please be aware that despite our efforts, no data security measures can guarantee 100% security at all time. Our systems and communications networks through which you access our Services may be subject to security breaches and failure which are due to circumstances beyond our reasonable control. If you have questions regarding the security of your personal information. please contact us.
When determining the measures for personal data security, We take into account the measures set forth by Article 19 of the Personal Data Law which may, in particular, include the following:

definition of threats to the security of the personal data when the personal data is processed in information systems of personal data;
application of organizational and technical measures to ensure the protection of the personal data when personal data is processed in information systems of personal data. These measures are required for compliance with requirements for the personal data protection established by the Government of the Russian Federation;
application of duly assessed security facilities;
evaluation of the effectiveness of the measures to ensure the protection of the personal data prior to putting it into operation the informational system of personal data;
accounting of the personal data medium facility;
detection of unauthorized access to the personal data and application of measures;
restoration of the personal data altered or destroyed in the result of unauthorized access;
set the rules of access to personal data processed in the information system of the personal data and ensure of users’ action with personal data logging in information system;
control over measures to ensure the protection of personal data and security level of the information system of the personal data.
In addition to security measures, We take some organizational measures required under the Personal Data Law to protect your information. In particular, we take into account requirements set forth in Article 18.1 of the Personal Data Law, including the following ones:

to appoint the Data protection officer;
to issue internal policies defining the Operator’s policy of personal data processing; documents related to personal data processing; other internal documents which define procedures aimed at preventing and detection of violations of the personal data legislation, remedy violations;
to perform legal, organizational and technical measures for the personal data protection in accordance with article 19 of the Personal data Law;
to provide internal control and (or) audit over compliance with the Personal data Law and its subordinate legislation, requirements for personal data protection, the Operator’s policy related to personal data processing, internal documents of the Operator;
to evaluate harm that may be caused to the Data subjects in the event of violation of the personal data legislation, matching such harm and measures aimed to ensure performance of obligations provided by law.
to inform the Operator’s staff, which actually processes the personal data, on provisions of the personal data legislation of the Russian Federation, including requirements for protection of the personal data, internal documents defining the Operator’s policy of personal data processing, other internal documents related to the personal data processing and (or) to train such staff.
